  "body": "React autobinds the methods of components created with `React.createClass`. But `Function.prototype.bind` is very slow on Chrome and Chromium derived browsers. Here is a post discussing it (http://benediktmeurer.de/2015/12/25/a-new-approach-to-function-prototype-bind/), and here is a adaption of the test code (https://jsfiddle.net/1kavbe7p/8/). One can test it on Google Chrome, finding that calling a bound function has an overhead even larger than heavy math computation.\n\nIt will be long before v8 fixes this long standing issue and for the new version to be adopted en masse. Meanwhile, React may improve its performance on Chrome by writing its own `bind`, just as in `lodash` or `underscore`.\n",
